<!-- CONCEPT + POLITICS -->
<section class="section" id="concept">
  <div class="two-col">
    <div class="copy-block">
      <h3>The Concept</h3>
      <p>Imagine walking past a large screen showing your neighbor transformed into a samurai in Japan, dancing at the Taj Mahal in India, or riding a mechanical bull in front of the American flag.</p>
      <div class="pull-quote">"Be A Global Citizen" seduces visitors into an AI-powered world tour of eight corporate-sponsored national stereotypes — and ends at a vending machine selling exclusively local Grand Rapids products.</div>
      <p>A personalized crypto-authenticated passport lets participants insert themselves into the fantasy, collect branded stamps featuring their own unique AI-generated images, and earn Global Citizenship.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="copy-block">
      <h3>The Political Context</h3>
      <p>This is not background — it is the work. Each of the eight country stations is brought to you by a multinational corporation with documented political spending through post-Citizens United super PACs and a specific extractive or exploitative history in that nation.</p>
      <p>Japan brought to you by Toyota Motor North America PAC. India by Dow. Saudi Arabia by ExxonMobil. The USA by Leading the Future PAC — the AI industry's own super PAC, which has raised tens of millions to elect candidates who will keep AI unregulated while its founders publicly champion responsible development.</p>
      <p>The AI generating these images exists inside that contradiction. This installation uses the same generative tools to make the mechanism visible.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

